      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure! The interest on your student loan is calculated monthly based on the remaining, unpaid balance. Even though the principal decreases each month with your payments, the interest is only applied to the reduced amount, leading to less overall reduction in the principal balance initially. As the outstanding principal decreases, the interest calculated each month becomes slightly lower, causing the principal reduction to eventually become more noticeable over time.",
